    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an impeccable 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), a definitive example of Zuffenhausen engineering. This specimen features the 3.6L flat-six M96 powerplant, delivering linear power through a crisp 6-speed Getrag manual transaxle. The mechanical integrity is absolute, featuring a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recently refreshed cooling system with a low-temperature thermostat. Suspension kinematics remain factory-spec with zero bushing deflection, ensuring the telepathic turn-in these chassis are known for. The exterior retains its original deep luster with no paint meter discrepancies, while the cabin shows zero bolster wear or pixel degradation on the instrumentation. A turn-key, investment-grade driver for the discerning purist.",
